pr_review_comment_body:
@nerogit 
no problem.

- But do you have any idea if there is fork repo or commit where secure url or `SAS` is enabled ?

@ragupta-git for code clarity it is better to try and reduce levels of indentation for the regular code path when applicable. this could be re-written as 
```
if not (condition):
    return
rest code of the code can start at the upper level again.
```

这段逻辑略复杂。p0 的处理部分是相对简单的，可以单独拿出来先处理掉（比如首先对 host 进行判断）
```
if host == 'p0.api.upyun.com':
    if method == 'GET':
         content = resp.json()
    else:
         content = resp.text
elif host == 'purge.upyun.com':
    content = resp.json()
elif multi:
    content = resp.json()
else:
    # rest and form api
   ....
    
```

这种 if-else 很多的逻辑一般把简单的放在前面，后面处理复杂的。另外，从 host 判断并不是个好选择（host 会有很多个，而且与这么长的字符串比较并不太好）。其实这个函数不作为入口的话，你可以直接加个 `kind` 参数表示来自哪类 api 请求。

If you created (I added this) a 

```
constructor(props: Props): void {
    super(props);
    ...
  }
```

isn't that redundant with that type definition at the top of class?

> Do we still need the null check here?

@camd - I think we do:
`TypeError: "selectJobController is null"`

I think I would put it in an `else:` clause after the except, so it is only run if there is not an exception. So this becomes:

```
try:
    os.makedirs(...)
except ....:
    ...
else:
    os.chown(...)
```

os.chown() is recursive, right? :)

@scanny Ok cool. I updated the commit. Much cleaner using that `CT_HdrFtrRef`.

I took the name from the analysis doc. I forget why we named it that but I think we probably had a good reason. Maybe.

Adding the `CT_HdrFtrRef` didn't fix the `r:id` cxml issue. Want to take a look?
